# Aipify Operating Principles

Read **[AIPIFY_GROUP_AS_COMPANY_FOUNDATION_DIRECTIVE.md](../../AIPIFY_GROUP_AS_COMPANY_FOUNDATION_DIRECTIVE.md)**, then **[CORE_FOUNDATION.md](../../CORE_FOUNDATION.md)** and **[OPERATING_PRINCIPLES.md](../../OPERATING_PRINCIPLES.md)** before new capabilities or agent skills.

## Governance order

1. **Company Foundation Directive** (Aipify Group AS — parent company identity)
2. **Core Foundation** (identity, mission, human control, privacy, core package)
3. **Operating Principles** (behaviour → communication → safety → escalation → learning → presence → skills)
4. **Architecture** ([ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) — layer, user, isolation, folder)
5. **Implementation**
6. **New operational skill** — only when foundation + principles are explicitly mapped

New capabilities must **never** bypass principles, plan limits, tenant isolation, or approval policy.

## Quick identity

Aipify is **install-first operational AI** inside customer systems — not a daily-login admin panel. *AI that works for your business.*

## Before a new skill or feature

- [ ] Fits identity (install-first, operational partner)
- [ ] Risk class assigned (`lib/core/risk.ts`); high/critical need human approval
- [ ] Plan module gated (`lib/core/plans.ts`)
- [ ] Learning uses approved metadata only — no PII/conversations
- [ ] Presence updated honestly when it runs
- [ ] Layer + folder decided per ARCHITECTURE.md

If any item is unclear, **pause** until decided.
